text:
i’ve got a thing for pills. .
.
.
i think about them a lot. every morning when i take them, i think about their power. i think about such a powerful little thing that has life altering effects. both good and bad.
.
.
.
bet you didn’t know i’m a drug addict. .
.
.
and not the kind that relies on daily medication to function in life (though i do need them for that too.)
.
.
.
i’m talking about the kind of addict that can’t fill a prescription for tooth pain due to fear of relapse. .
.
.
the kind where my fiancé has to hide my potentially life threatening prescriptions and dose them out to me only when necessary because i can’t handle it myself.
.
.
.
i was “sick” a lot in high school and college. for the first time ever, i’m coming out and admitting that most of those illnesses were overdose induced.
.
.
.
i still struggle when i find a stray pill. i probably always will. addicts are always in recovery.
.
.
.
but there is recovery. there is support. and there is hope.
.
.
.
i’m here by god’s grace and it’s time i start being honest with you in hopes that it might help even just ☝️ person. .
.
.
be strong. it sucks. but it is worth it.

text:
consent- a word i used to associate with having a legal guardian signing a form to go on a school trip! years later i learnt another meaning. i want to share my story with you as a preventative measure. i used to believe that sexual assault or rape couldn’t be at the hands of a friend, until it happened to me. i gave someone my trust and they broke that, worse still i brushed it under the carpet and blamed myself for putting myself in that situation. i was held against my will and had literal as well as figurative bruises, my boyfriend at the time never found out and i had to live with it. 
tonight, i was on a bus and a man thought it was perfectly okay to grab my arse just cause i happened to step into his way to let a lady off. i turned around and asked “can i help you?” i then sat down he preceded to use gestures to indicate my figure (while i was in a long trench coat). this is not okay, we still live in a world where this is tolerated.
as small or as insignificant anyone may think it is, whether someone has cat called you or grabbed your bollocks! (yes men are victims too) do not stand for it. 
#metoo #consent #sex #sexualassult #women #girls #men #consentissexy #yes #knowtheline

text: in this picture, taken in 1942 during world war ii, dad is third from the right. it's a huge synchronicity that this veteran's day i'm in berlin for the first time, to present at the 2018 fascia research congress on connective tissue, interoception, and emotional health. (this makes me think of the social epigenetics of trauma, wherein trauma is passed down through generations.) it's hard to walk these streets without feeling an intense remembrance deep in the layers of my tissue and in the marrow of my bones, of the oppression that my family (my mother and her family in particular) suffered at the hands of this country and its leadership and in the name of freedom. the oppression that looms again in germany's growing problematic ideologies- and those of the .u.s. the oppression that continues unabated in the u.s. and has existed throughout its history, from invasion in 1492 until today, in the country i live in. this day we remember those who fought for our liberation, for a better life beyond the duration of their own. this remembrance also evokes the countless battles for liberation that continue today because they have not yet been won: the battle for freedom and equality for black, indigenous and people of color, women, and vulnerable bodies, for true social equity. nationalism is on the rise in germany, in the u.s., and elsewhere. may we stand up and do our part in this battle, to fight for the lives that will live beyond our own. 🙏🏼 #neverforget #fightoppression #fightracism #socialjustice #neuronerd #yogaworkshop #shakethesystem #itspolitical #yogaforemotionalbalance  #embodiment #emotionalbalance #interoception #healing #bodyjustice #decolonizingyoga #yoga #yogaeverydamnday #fearless #decolonizethebody #boforbesyoga #ibelieveher #nobinaries #posttraumaticgrowth #metoo #wetoo

text:
słyszeliście o awanturze w programie ameryka express? powiem wam, że za nim jeszcze była akcja #metoo przychodziłam do domu wielokrotnie oburzona zachowaniem niektórych panów zarówno na siłowni oraz innych miejscach i opowiadałam o tym mężowi 😞 i oczywiście wiem, że kobiety mają swoje za uszami. wiele z nich doskonale wie co robi i wykorzystuje sytuację... o oceny na studiach dziewczyny potrafiły wypinać się przed profesorem, a co dopiero o rolę filmie w stanach! nie chce mi się wierzyć, że wszystkie były molestowane.... ale problem jest... panowie za dużo sobie pozwalają, co więcej myślą, że są zabawni i przebojowi.... dostaję kilkanaście wiadomości dziennie!!! niektóre po prostu są poniżej jakiegokolwiek poziomu... a ja nie chodzę wulgarnie ubrana ani umalowana, nie wstawiam wyzywających zdjęć na fb ani na instagramie. na siłowni nie wypinam się przed chłopakami tylko ćwiczę z boku... ale nawet gdyby tak było, jeśli mówię nie - nie narzucaj się... napisał do mnie całkiem niedawno na insta piłkarz z izraelu, który był w kieleckim hotelu, że mogę przyjechać - nikt się o niczym nie dowie, on za 2 dni wyjeżdża... wiadomości dostawałam tyle, że musiałam go zablokować! facet, którego stać na zaspokojenie potrzeb w różny sposób 😉 dostał dosłownie małpiego rozumu 🤦🏽‍♀️ odmowa jeszcze bardziej go nakręcała.. i sytuacja z rolando w ogóle mnie nie dziwi. niektórzy myślą, że mogą wszystko... nie wiem czy to jest wina tego, że dziewczyny wszędzie się rozbierają za lajki i facetom wszystko się już miesza - rzeczywistość z życiem wirtualnym? 
wracają do programu tvn zachowanie młodego chajzera wiele razy było chamskie. i całowanie kogokolwiek bez jego zgody jest molestowaniem (wiecej na moim fb - link w bio).
.
.
.

from the emerging #metoo series:

though she can't speak--or is afraid to speak-- and therefore the bird as messenger has the man on the run, she none-the-less told me last night that she wasn't quite finished after our work together in the studio. 
she needed a pattern on her clothing, one that was fashionable, yet reminiscent of chains.  and she needed a feminine crown that links her to stereotypical domesticity. one of my beloved vintage pudding molds fit the bill.

can you find the suggestion of a dead bird?

text: depression and anxiety look a lot alike and you can have both at the same time. it can be very confusing and it is just one of the reasons i don’t like labels.  when you feel horrible, a label isn’t as important as figuring out what to do to feel better.  anxiety can create depression because it takes so much energy to push down the anxious feelings that it can leave us exhausted and numb.  there is something in the dsm, the manual used for diagnosis, called atypical depression that describes characteristics of both depression and anxiety.  anxiety creates physical symptoms because it impacts sleep, the adrenal glands, the heart, the gut, the skin and potentially other organs.  not feeling well physically can also make us feel depressed, out of control of our own lives and very tired.  i encourage you to try to stay with your feelings, rather than pushing them down, even if they are painful.  when we avoid things, we make them more powerful and more frightening.  we can’t help ourselves if we don’t know what we are dealing with.  love to hear about your experiences and thoughts. ❤️ #anxiety #anxietyrelief #anxietyrecovery #anxietyhelp #depression #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthrecovery #nostigma #nofear #jungianpsychology #carljung #eatingdisorderrecovery #emotionaleating #emotionaleatingrecovery #trauma #sexualabuse #metoo #katiebeecher #medicalintuitive #goop #goopwellness #spiritualhealing #healfromwithin

text:
the world has already ended and you may die!!! dr. bones1 year ago
“the ‘we can stop this from happening’ part of the story is over. it’s already happened.” from dr. bones
i imagine they held hands before they fell to their deaths.

maybe there was a quiet moment shared between two lovers, an acknowledgement of all they’d been through. perhaps there was a single tear and a calm squeeze of the hand. it’d all be okay, he says, we’ll be together and we won’t have to worry.

a pained smile, a small, almost depressing laugh. yes, together. i love you.

i love you too, he says.

and then they step forward.

it was a small fall, all things considered, but certainly enough to do the job. i don’t know if you’ve ever heard what a falling body sounds like, but you can go into your kitchens right now, wet a rag, and throw it against the ground. in the pockets of their crumpled corpses were found two notes, both in plastic bags so they wouldn’t be soaked in blood. one had the title “we had a wonderful life.’’ full article: godsandradicals.org

text:
20塊布m巾完成！

感恩能參與製作這批布衞生巾，是無比的福氣，因為我們有選擇！幸福的我們，如何能夠想像，在地球的某個角落，竟然有少女要用自己的身體，去換取我們能輕易購買得到的日常衞生用品！

一邊車縫這批布衞生巾，一邊默默地為這些女孩祈禱，想著她們的經歷，是何等的心痛！

希望我們能付出更多，做到更多，去改善這些婦女的生活！讓她們得到正確的衞生知識和性教育，讓她們知道自己的身體是多麼的寶貴！願當地政府能正視這些社會問題。

text:
💕💛🕉🦋🌻🌼this weekend i was blessed to complete trauma informed outreach training by the connection coalition with an amazing group of inspired women. i came to the training with only a desire to serve, but i walked away a transformed person after a weekend of connection, vulnerability, healing, expressing, releasing, supporting, listening, and learning. 
in summary, i learned how to identify the various ways in which trauma affects the body, mind, and collective soul. i also learned how the power of connection opens the way to healing for all, and practical ways to facilitate this process for myself and others.

healing from trauma is a lifelong journey of self-discovery, self-inquiry, self-expression, and self-love. we are constantly evolving, unfolding, and becoming, our coping mechanisms evolve as well - therefore the process of personal healing must follow suit! the more we learn about ourselves, especially through relationships, the better equipped we are to grow into our own vision of peace, happiness and success. 💯supporting others in their healing is also a part of our growth. it is not an act of heroism - but instead an acknowledgment of their light. through our contributions of service leadership, we send a clear message to others that we see them as competent and capable of finding solutions, cultivating resources and integrating strategies to creating the life they want.

i am grateful for the opportunity to witness and participate in this training with such a beautiful group of souls who seek to give, serve, lead, and share the wealth.

i am also grateful to facilitation & trainings manager, marisol tamez, who kept it raw and real while sharing her brilliance in a way that uplifted, informed, and inspired everyone in attendance!

finally, i salute the connection coalition and its leadership team for making this opportunity available in cities all around the us.

in peace & beauty,
dominique 👉p.s. download my free 15-minute guided meditation to start your week on a positive note at @rohiniwellness (link in bio) or visit bit.ly/igmeditation

text:
we need to be more compassionate and more caring with children. instead of asking children, “what's wrong with you?” ask the child, “what happened to you? if somebody would have asked questions to me in a loving and compassionate way i would have probably told someone that i was being sexually abused. but what i often heard people say to me was “what’s wrong with you? you are a very rebellious and a very problematic child.” in my mind i would respond, “nothing is wrong with me... i am being sexually abused. what’s wrong with you that you choose to ignore my desperate outcries asking for help.”

text:
i’m doing @vivalamoure ‘s 6 day #nakedwerise challenge. i did it last year too and i really enjoyed the writing prompts. day one is truth. what is your truth despite anything else that has happened? how can you tell your body “i am safe to release this pain now, i love you, i am so sorry. i am leaning into my strength now.” •
when i think of my truth i think of being made aware, choosing to see all the things that have kept me from it. i have to be willing to witness where i’m at now in order to see that i’m not living my truth. clarity about where i am now seems like step one to me. next comes visualizing, feeling in my body what it would be like to live my truth so that i can get closer to it. in my heart i’m a creator, a mover, and a teacher. these are the things i want to amplify in my life. my truth is that i have something to offer the world, and i am so excited to do that. i am safe now to be who i am. i forgive myself for being scared of my path, for thinking i’m not good enough to do it. i’m so sorry that i put myself down for years and didn’t believe in myself. i am ready to lean into my strength now and accomplish all that my heart desires. i honor my heart. •
•
•
#truth #mytruth #whattheheartwants #vulnerability #learntolisten #selflove #ilovemyself #iamenough #iamworthy #whoami #honoryourself #honoryourheart #oregoncoast #portraitshot #portraitphotography #iseeyou #iampowerful #femininerising #metoo #sacredfeminine #womenrising #reclaiming #followyourheart #leadership #selfleadership #innerknowing #innerguidance

when i think of my truth i think of being made aware, choosing to see all the things that have kept me from it. i have to be willing to witness where i’m at now in order to see that i’m not living my truth. clarity about where i am now seems like step one to me. next comes visualizing, feeling in my body what it would be like to live my truth so that i can get closer to it. in my hea i’m a creator, a mover, and a teacher. these are the things i want to amplify in my life. my truth is that i have something to offer the world, and i am so excited to do that. i am safe now to be who i am. i forgive myself for being scared of my path, for thinking i’m not good enough to do it. i’m so sorry that i put myself down for years and didn’t believe in myself. i am ready to lean into my strength now and accomplish all that my hea desires. i honor my hea. •
•
•

text:
happy #membermonday to the incredible community to community development, a wscadv member program in bellingham, wa. c2c approaches their work by the people, for the people. their programs are ever changing to meet the needs of the community. c2c works with youth, women and people of color to create strong communities, cultivating safe food and labor systems and strong, healthy families and relationships. they work to:

empower under-represented peoples to have an equal voice in decision making processes

develop cross-cultural awareness
restore justice to our food, land and cultural practices

promote community relationships towards self-reliance

work in solidarity with those that strive towards human rights for all

rescue the value of feminine intellect and leadership

c2c has partnered with wscadv in concern for the high rates of sexual assault in agricultural worksites. “what are we going to do as labor to hold each other accountable for ensuring that women are not being sexually harassed?” guillen asked. “there has to be a discussion about how men identify a sexually offensive comment or behavior. and if you don’t identify it that way, but a woman does, we need to ask, ‘why?'” -c2c executive director rosalinda guillen

advocates across the state have been taking lessons learned from c2c and going into labor camps and packing sheds to ask the same question, break up isolation, and build promatora style educational and advocacy programs. 
community organization and restorative justice is how c2c is working to #enddv and call #timesup on sexual violence.

text:
one of the ancient stories that pops up in my mind is the tales of the pandora’s box. we learn that if some action is taken, it will “open pandora’s box” or cause some terrible thing to happen that cannot be undone. the pandora box of horror that i revealed to the police was life changing because i had to choose to lose my family or choose to save myself and other potential victims in my family from being sexually abused by my father. during the time that i broke the silence i suffered much pain, loneliness and backlash from my family but i will never regret breaking the silence. i will always commend myself for being such a brave little girl. it has been four decades after my abuse and i still continue to open the pandora box and unleash the hidden crimes in our communities. these life altering crimes that people want to sweep under the rug and that is still a tabu for many families to speak about around the world. i still face adversity and animosity from people who want to silence me, but i will continue to break the silence and defend innocent children at all cost even if it means to stand alone. i will also continue to speak out for those survivors who still remain in silence in hope that one day they too can open the pandora box of lies, betrayal and evil so they can at least be free from carrying that painful burden of the sexual abuse.

text:
after a gruelling month of midterms and term papers, i am back with my review of women talking by miriam toews!✨
______________________________________
there is no time like the present to read a book like this one. the topics discussed, although taking place in a rural mennonite community, are relevant to all women across the globe. there are so many characters with unique personalities that are sometimes hard to keep track of, but intriguing nonetheless. there is also a lack of quotation marks (a huge pet peeve of mine) which makes things confusing at times. the ending is beautiful, both from a metaphorical and literal perspective. if you’re interested in the #metoo movement, or even just someone who loves some good female representation, this is your book. 
______________________________________
if you want to read my full review for this book, check out the link in my bio!🔗
______________________________________

text:
'i feel really low.' i texted you few hours ago, it was 3pm. also i was texting a friend, though i didn't plan on telling him that i'm not in a very nice mood but i somehow managed to mention and he says, let's catch up. i tried refusing but he insisted. so, i said fine. i checked if you saw my text or not and i realised you liked a post six minutes back. i do my regular skin care, standing in front of the mirror, thinking to go for bold lips or eyes with the super lacy maroon dress you gifted. i received a notification, it was still him. 'i'll be a little late, it's work. making it soon for you.' i rolled my eyes.
i called you, you didn't receive. i sighed, you might be busy. i was perturbed by your capricious behaviour that evening when it was really not a new thing for me. in my lace dress, a little bold eyes and subtle lip, he picks me up and he wanted to taste the new food place around the corner. gradually, he's driving at an unusual speed. i ask him to go slow, he snubs me. i question him. the place is dead. you can't really tell if a human has ever passed by and till then he cups my breasts and i slap him. i tell him you'll kill him the time i'll tell you about this. i tell him how you never wanted me to see him but yet i did, and he's such an asshole. he pins both of my hands up in the air in his one hand, aggressively holding my face, tryin his best for our lips to touch. i remember punching him, constantly yelling and that is when he slapped me. i had tears in my eyes but i think i had never been more angrier before. my blood was burning, and in a very low pitch voice, i question him, "how dare you?" he grabbed me by my hair and pulled it even harder, biting my neck, leaving marks. his phone rings and he's holding me recklessly, as my head bleeds. as he hangs up the call, he leaves me with a warning to never utter a word to you. i would have. i wanted to. i waited with hope for you. i walked to home. numb in silence. i took a shower with my clothes on, still shivering. and then, you were online three minutes ago, and i knew you were not busy anymore. 
it's 3am now, i'm in bed asleep, and you reply, "why?"
i wanted to talk, i would've, not anymore.
name: Priyanka.

text:
i rörelse - dagboken, 24 maj 2014
.
.
"det är som om luften tagit slut. inget syre kvar i det här huset. x och jag pratar knappt med varandra längre. vi är inte osams men ingenting jag har att säga känns relevant. när jag är på övervåningen är han på undervåningen och tvärtom. jag har planerat att lämna honom i ett helt år snart. jag har inte orkat. inte kunnat. väntar och väntar på rätt tillfälle. jag kommer att förlora allt jag har. är maktlös och helt beroende av honom. har inga pengar och ingenstans att ta vägen. men - jag kan inte leva i den här lögnen längre nu. inte efter det som hände i natt.

vi lägger oss i sängen, som vanligt utan vidare beröring. jag försöker undkomma det starka skenet från hans läsplatta. mina tysta tårar gör kudden sur och kall. han märker inte. läsplattan släcks. rummet blir mörkt. precis så mörkt det är inuti mig. jag somnar, våt om ansiktet.
.
.
jag vaknar till av att min kropp är i rörelse utan att jag själv rör en muskel. det är så mörkt, kanske är det halv fyra, det känns så. jag hör xs andetag bakom mig. jag vaknar lite mer. hans lem är hård och glider in och ut mellan mina lår. jag känner hur mitt kön är varmt och vått av hans fukt. jag förstår inte. jag sover ju? hans händer runt min midja. han bökar under täcket. som ett djur. stönar. grymtar. min kropp glider fram och tillbaka på lakanet. har vi sex? jag fattar inte. jag sover ju? jag är inte vaken. är jag vaken? han fortsätter att såga sig in och ut ur mig. sågar itu allt som känns verkligt. jag vet inte varför vi har sex. jag sover ju. känner mig inte det minsta upphetsad. mörkret runt mig är ingenting jämfört med det jag känner just nu. min kropp som rör sig utan att jag styr. stötvis. är jag ett stycke kött? känner mig rå och styckad. han stönar. han njuter. jag är kissnödig. törstig. jag vill skrika. jag vill försvinna. domna bort. efteråt somnar jag om. .
.sömnen känns mer trygg än min verklighet just nu."
.
.
"no memories of my crying bed" (mia makila, 2017, digital collage).
.
.

text:
ladies here’s the facts: most ‘good’ guys, guys who want commitment, love, marriage, just one woman, are doing it from a place of insecurity! where are all the good men? they’re in your friends zone (have known you for months/years but too scared to tell you how they feel), they are at the bar/club/party/dating app but too scared to approach you because fear of rejection, fear you have a boyfriend, fear of #metoo etc. good guys are usually shy and beta and these guys let fear of negative results stop them from going after what they want!
confident bad boys jerks fuck boys womanizers are fearless. they go after what they want. no fear of rejection or me too. they don’t care if you have a boyfriend or husband (they’ll still try to fuck you)! these are the only guys that approach.  men by nature don’t want just one woman. just like animals. monogamy is a human thing created by women. a truly confident man doesn’t want commitment because he knows he can pull multiple women. an insecure man knows he doesn’t possess the looks, money or charm to pull women so he must lock one down, anyone down, out of fear he will end up alone. 
so what happens to insecure good guys, they are in the friend zone, they don’t approach at all. or they approach with just enough fake confidence and charm to get your number and ask you out but on the first date something is off...she senses his neediness and says no to a second date since she felt no ‘spark’. 🤔
women will always choose the confident guy who treats them bad over the insecure guy who treats them good. women by nature are wired to be drawn to confidence. even when it constantly makes them choose the guys who hurt them. 
this is why i made no more mr. nice guy. to teach good guys how to be confident. the only other answer would be for women to start being turned on by genuine-ness than by swagger....good luck 😤

text:
off to la in head to toe sustainable fashion for two days of fashion, sustainability and (i hope) inspiring climate change solutions for the fashion industry at the @remode conference. i admit i’m not thrilled about traveling to a sustainability event via plane, especially to a state experiencing the effects of climate change first hand with the deadliest wildfire in its history.  i hope that this devastating backdrop pushes attendees and speakers to aggressively, uncompromisingly, and unapologetically adopt and share radical ideas for change. i hope the change discussed is systemic and not surface, inclusive and not elitist and above all, wildly creative. the problems we face are a matter of life and death and tinkering with the status quo is not going to cut it. #fashionneedsanewnarrative #makeearthgreenagain #fashionrevolution 🌏🌊💚
head to @lafdfoundation and donate whatever you can.

text:
i never had “the talk”. i don’t know if it’s a racial thing, family thing, or just plain scared thing. whatever it was i let the trend end with me. i had the talk with my daughter when she was 9. not just the birds and bees but the real side of #growingupagirl. 
i applaud the women of the #metoo movement but i’m raising my daughter to say #notme. i will not pass on the legacy of letting boys be boys, and he hit you because he likes you. in my book that damn girl stuff. i tell the stories of my #metoo moments and i set them free.

let’s be a bit more transparent with our daughters without bashing our sons. it’s her world to create i just want it to be comfortable in it. 
if you want to read about our conversations and my ordeals click the link in my bio or go to @amazon or @apple ibooks.

text:
nightmares. by far the worst thing about my ptsd. i have them at least 3 or 4 times a week lately.
i'm often afraid to fall asleep. i'd rather have no sleep than these nightmares. i don't want to relive everything, every single detail. 
when i was younger, my mom had to wake me up when i had nightmares because i was crying and screaming. now i wake up on my own without screaming, just crying.
when im sleeping in the same bed with someone or at least in the same room with someone, i don't have nightmares or only like once a week. i don't know if i feel protected or something.
the worst nightmares i have after a night out with lots of alcohol. when i was on holiday with my friends i drank way too much alcohol and i had the worst nightmare in a long time. i woke up crying and i panicked because i was alone in that room and for a moment i didn't know where i was. i really should drink less alcohol.
i really hope that one day i won't be afraid to fall asleep .
.

this three-performance event is a gift from playwright alyson mead, who in the wake of conversations about consent, sexual assault and rape has graciously given special permission to perform her timely play "the flora and the fauna" across the nation. 
all tickets have a $10 suggested donation and all proceeds go to benefit the #metoo movement. 
additional performances at:
nov 18 / union
nov 20 / apollon 
for more information:
402.554.2430 | steven_williams@unomaha.edu

text:
hillary clinton will run for white house again in 2020, says former adviser
hillary clinton is all but certain to run for the white house again in 2020, according to a former aide.

mark penn said the democrat had “an unfinished mission to be the first female president” and “a personal grievance” against donald trump, who vowed to imprison her before emerging victorious in the 2016 vote. “she will not allow this humiliating loss at the hands of an amateur to end the story of her career,” he wrote in a wall street journal article co-authored by former democrat politician andrew stein.  mr penn was a senior aide to ms clinton and her husband bill from 1995 to 2008 and was chief strategist for her failed campaign for the democratic nomination a decade ago.

ms clinton has previously insisted she would not seek to run again, although last month she appeared to hint at a change of stance, admitting: “i’d like to be president.” mr penn and mr stein said the former secretary of state “has had two years to go over what she did wrong” in 2016 and would “come out swinging” with a strategy for defeating mr trump. “you can expect her to run for president once again,” they wrote. “maybe not at first, when the legions of senate democrats make their announcements, but definitely by the time the primaries are in full swing.” ms clinton would reinvent herself as a liberal firebrand to “easily” capture the democratic nomination, mr penn and mr stein predicted. “she will hope to emerge as an unstoppable force to undo mr trump, running on the #metoo movement, universal health care and gun control,” they wrote.

long-time confidants of ms clinton poured hot water on the prediction she would run again in two years. “she’s more likely to win powerball,” philippe reines, her former adviser, told the hill.

but mr penn and mr stein said: “don’t pay much attention to the ‘i won’t run’ declarations. mrs clinton knows both mr clinton and mr obama declared they weren’t running, until they ran.” kellyanne conway, one of donald trump’s most senior advisers, mocked the idea of ms clinton’s comeback. “dear god, please, yes,” she tweeted with a link to the story.

text:
i know for a fact that the tantric approach to sexuality can help heal the social attitude that allows rape to even be a consideration for men.
the conventional belief about rape is that it is not a crime of sex, it is a crime of power. i do not believe this is entirely true. sometimes the crossing of boundaries which constitutes “non-consensual sex,” i.e. rape, really is about the perpetrator meeting a need for sexual gratification, and they simply do not value or care about the needs of the other person, and have not been taught to recognize or value engaged and mutual consent.
this is exactly the wound to which tantra can be applied.
the tantric approach to sex (and all of life really), begins with your motivation, i.e your primary reason for taking action. any action, be it sexual or non-sexual.
in many forms of sexual tantra, the primary motivation for sexual play is the connection- to deepen, enhance, cultivate, celebrate, ‘bliss out’ on the feeling of connection and oneness between you and your partner/s.

read how tantra can heal rape culture here: http://bit.ly/rape-tantra

#sexualhealing #rape #metoo #sex #power #tantra #authentictantra #connection

text:
**insecurity manifests differently**
•
•
one of the hardest things to understand is why someone would rape or sexually assault someone. when a man does that to a woman, he is literally penetrating himself into her body without her permission [sorry if that was graphic]. it’s fucked up and confusing.
•
•
we hear all sorts of reasons as to why someone would violate another human that way, and most of them are a mask for the real issue. i won’t say “none”, but very few men...no matter how “alpha” they are would rape someone for power, or pride, or even carnal desire. it’s [almost] always a manifestation of their insecurities…the boss might take advantage of the “new hot girl” because he thinks he has the power to do that, but this is driven by something much deeper. •
•
when i was in a situation where a woman asked me to stop it wasn’t because my dick was already hard, or because i was going to get what i wanted however i could...it was the feeling of rejection that spiked my insecurity & made me desperate to find a way to be embraced by this human. so i slowed us way down, kissed her softly and let her lead me to a place she was safe & we could continue from. what i did that night is a form of sexual assault. it’s something i had to live with, admit to myself i had done, & learn from because i knew it wasn’t ok. •
•
men - we must stand up in the midst of our guilt & shame, stare our insecurities in the face, own up to the shit we’ve done & walk forward in a new sense of freedom. my heart breaks every time i hear/read #metoo stories & the only way to stop these stories is for us (men) to own our shit. 
#starttoday #therapy #mentalhealthawareness #insecurity #ibelieveher #illgofirst #selftosociety

text:
as the #metoo movement continues to gather force, and female stars wear black to the golden globe awards, this screening and workshop pauses to reflect on some of the female filmmakers who have preceded the current furore, using film to campaign for feminism, and feminism as the underlying force, in films which range from the confrontational and personal, to the experimental and poetic.

the artist, curator and writer lucy reynolds shares her research into feminist filmmaking in an evening and afternoon of screenings and discussion – plucking books from glasgow women’s library film section, and films from the lux and cinenova collections, to illuminate the diverse ways in which film has been shaped by feminist debate, and the concerns of women’s lived experience.

find out more via our website, link in bio.

organised in partnership with @womenslibrary 
image credit: susan stein, tracks, 1989. courtesy the artist and cinenova

#feministfilm #womeninfilm #fisforfeminism

text:
thank you, michelle obama for becoming.

i walked into a quiet, empty bookstore, thinking it would be a great time to pitch my book, operation growth. if there aren’t any customers, maybe i can help with that, right?! wrong.

the bookstore owners asked me to tell her about my book. i explained it was a memoir about overcoming challenges and trauma in life and still living with joy and purpose. she told me that was not a unique story and started looking me up in her computer. “is your book available in my system?” yes, it is. you can order it directly from the publisher, which really was me. “well, it’s priced too high for me to order it and sell it here. you can bring a few in and we can see how they sell.” i started doing figures in my head. how can i keep up with leaving a few books at multiple bookstores and work my job. nah, not worth it. besides, she said my story isn’t unique. it feels unique to me and i really hope it helps other people to grow. 
did i just spend thousands of dollars to produce a book that no one will find worthwhile? and then countless others told their stories as well and #metoo came back with a vengeance. there was gabrielle union and jenifer lewis and now there is michelle obama!

just the quotes from her book before it’s even available are receiving so much love from so many! and there it is...i wasn’t wrong to write it. maybe i wasn’t famous enough or just a bit too early, but not wrong. it’s important that we tell our honest stories to support our daughter and sons and the next generation. so thanks to all those who’ve written their own growth stories...i salute you and stand with you. thank you!!! brandi r. richard has spoken to thousands of people across the united states and the world and offers strategies to individuals and for-profit, governmental, and non-profit organizations. her clients characterize her as altruistic, down-to-earth, impavid, and powerful. she is an award-winning leader, author of operation growth, and co-host of angela carr patterson’s soulful conversations. learn more about brandi at www.brcomm.co.
name: Future Brandi R. Thompson

text_retweet:
please see her page for additional comments and the full story. #repost @irmingardmayer with @get_repost
・・・
the actions of cristian buitron are sickening and uncomfortably distressing. while i never experienced sexual assault in his presence, looking back there were warning signs of his true nature. hearing stories from other women has brought up painful memories of that inner voice in my head that i chose to ignore. and for that, i regret.
•
before i share my own story. i want to stress…. it is never the victim’s responsibility to explain or dissect and share their experience of sexual assault. i appreciate the bravery of every woman who has come forward. it takes an unimaginable amount of strength to do this. their words are powerful and have initiated opportunity for healing and change. but i also respect the choice of anyone to work through their experience in privacy with family, friends and therapy.
•
i knew cristian through the community. he shot with many of my friends and co-workers. he shot events at the studio i teach at. when he asked me to shoot it seemed like a normal progression. i assumed through the plethora of connections that he was to be trusted. he wanted to do a body paint shoot. i was not really interested in this. i didn’t find these images to be that appealing or the concept especially original. i would have preferred to just shoot fitness photos. but i figured since he was the photographer and i was not paying for the shoot that if i agreed to shoot, it would have to be in the direction of his vision.
•
so we arranged a shoot date. i cancelled the day before we were supposed to meet. i just had this bad feeling. we rescheduled. i let him know my reservations about the body paint aspect. he told me i could think about it and bring other clothing options to shoot in. he also told me to bring shoes i didn’t mind getting covered in paint in case i changed my mind about the body painting. (continued below)

text:
the power of living in the now.

ok, this is difficult...for me. i'm still learning about mindfulness and living in the present moment rather than having my mind in the past or future. living in the now makes sense, and calms the depressive thoughts of the past and the worrying thoughts and anxieties about the future. so my mental health does improve while practicing mindfulness and living in the moment.

imagine if you actually lived in the now. how would your life and health be different? i found when i was living in africa it was easier to live in the now. it helped that the cultural norm was to live in the now, versus in western culture we are often in the mindset of the future.

this is a work in progress for me.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
meet ariana delawari this wed nov 14th, an afghan american filmmaker, musician and activist.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
her award-winning feature-length directorial debut 'we came home', was just released and on sale now on itunes by time. the film is a culmination of her documentation of afghanistan since 9/11, her family story, and the making of her album lion of panjshir. lion of panjshir was recorded in both kabul and los angeles. delawari collaborated with a few american bandmates and three afghan elder master musicians. the album was partially produced and mixed by filmmaker david lynch. lynch released the critically acclaimed album on his record label. we came home film won the grand jury prize at sao paulo international film festival, the jury prize at mexico international film festival, the jury award at rajasthan international film festival, the echoes of earth award at flickers : rhode island international film festival, and screened at many festivals around the world including afi fest, afi docs, al jazeera documentary film festival, the united nations film festival, and the international film festival of india. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
i don’t usually put up posts like these, but after the stuff i’ve been coming across these past few days, somehow this seemed important to voice.
(if you start, please read till the end) 
i wholeheartedly support the #metoo movement. i admire those who are strong enough to speak up and i sympathize and empathize with their cause. i too have been harassed on more than one occasion and live everyday with the fear of it happening again. unfortunately we live in a world where some men are more “animal” than they are human, and i believe every dog has their day. 
however, i am also very lucky to have some decent men in my life: my dad, grandad, brother, fiance, cousins, uncles, and the wonderful guys i get to call my friends.. i can’t speak for everyone.. and i understand that not everyone is what they seem, people change for the better and for the worse, but i do believe that atleast 1 out of 100 men, is decent.

today, i speak for them. for all those who are put in a category that they genuinely do not belong in. for all those men that are afraid to let go of the handle bars on the bus or train for fear of falling on the girl standing next to them and hearing an earful afterwards. for all those men who keep their eyes on the ground at all times, for fear of having someone accuse them of staring inappropriately. for all those men who have fought to protect a woman. for all those men who give any and all women their due respect and sometimes much more. here’s to those men. 
let’s not forget, we’re in an era where men and women are equal. if we don’t like to be categorized, why are we doing it to them? 
i hope by sharing my thoughts we realize that there can be more to this conversation. #notallmen
name: UmmeSalama Shabbar - ItsMyType

however, i am also very lucky to have some decent men in my life: my dad, grandad, brother, fiance, cousins, uncles, and the wonderful guys i get to call my friends.. i can’t speak for everyone.. and i understand that not everyone is what they seem, people change for the better and for the worse, but i do believe that atleast 1 out of 100 men, is decent.

today, i speak for them. for all those who are put in a category that they genuinely do not belong in. for all those men that are afraid to let go of the handle bars on the bus or train for fear of falling on the girl standing next to them and hearing an earful afterwards. for all those men who keep their eyes on the ground at all times, for fear of having someone accuse them of staring inappropriately. for all those men who have fought to protect a woman. for all those men who give any and all women their due respect and sometimes much more. here’s to those men. 
let’s not forget, we’re in an era where men and women are equal. if we don’t like to be categorized, why are we doing it to them? 
i hope by sharing my thoughts we realize that there can be more to this conversation. #notallmen

metoo keppel находят поклонников среди всех возрастов. им будет рада и студентка, и домохозяйка и школьница. сражают наповал неповторимым обаянием и нежностью.

высота игрушки: 48 см
материал: высококачественный мягкий плюш, трикотаж
наполнитель: технологичный полипропиленовый хлопок, производства южной кореи.
можно стирать в стиральной машинке на деликатном режиме.

text:
i can’t stress this enough when we’re faced with divorce. it’s imperative that we don’t have “yes” people surrounding us, that we don’t have judgemental people hurting us, that we aren’t lying about our circumstances to win favour, that we don’t have to hide who we are and that we have people around us who are surrounding us with love and support and who bring out the best in us and push us to be stronger, greater and happier! *
*
we will be faced with some hard conversations and parting of ways with some people once you raise this standard, and i can’t stress to you enough how important it is to hold this standard high. *
*
anyone who loves you will want to support and help you in any way they can, not find reasons to judge or torment you if you’re not living your life their way.*

text:
it’s one thing to crack down on overt harassment and assault. offhand remarks and uncomfortable moments are another story.

they're the sorts of behaviors that can be awkward to talk about and hard to define. the #metoo movement has helped create space for those conversations, but it doesn’t mean colleges have figured out how to deal with behaviors that aren’t black or white.

those uncomfortable moments have consequences. over time, they weigh people down. julia york, a graduate student, was tired of being silent, tired of whispering. she pushed her department to reckon with the subtle forms of sexism that can make women question their place in the academy. follow the link in our bio to read more of her story. 📸: @tamirhasacellphone

text:
you educate a girl, you can change a nation! my mission for love’ u inc has always been to educate, encourage & empower women & young girls! 🌎
.
.
.
💡educate: i was able to speak to a room full of teens & their moms, informing them on the cycle of violence (tension building, explosion, honeymoon). using my story to further remind them if he did it before he will do it again. .
.
.
🗣encourage: i encouraged all of them to not only speak up if ever abused, but to never allow any one to abuse them physically, mentally, emotionally or verbally. .
.
.
✨empower: i empowered these young girls to know that they are worthy! they deserve nothing but the best and if their partner can’t give them that, then they simply aren’t the one for them! 
#educateagirlempoweranation #tsrmorninginspiration #teengirls #teendatingviolence #cycleofviolence #hewilldoitagain #bebrave #speakup #metoo #youareenough #abuseisabuse #verbalabuse #physicalabuse #financialabuse #emotionalabuse #mentalabuse #loveyou #empower #womenempowerment #empoweredwomenempower

text:
i’m #winning y tengo #angelesconmigo. estoy en #aguadilla, un lugar con gente linda y generous. esta ciudad es useful for mi proyecto #decolonialbiznessworld given the joint “civil-military airport.” btw there is nothing #civil about the #military. #fucktheusmilitary. 
#guayama is, of course, not near aguadilla, and that’s where i’ll head in time. it is #3 hours away. it is famous for its #brujas, its #witches. 
my abuela me llegó aquí para ver la realidad colonial y la manera en que la gente viven con dignidad y elegancia. también es importante para la #calculación de #reparaciones y el proceso descolonial en acción.
the violence we experience as individuals is always shared by other people and communities, yet how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this #earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

calculating reparations is always an economic and spiritual practice.

above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to create solutions for ourselves and our beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective, what aspects of healing can financial reparations facilitate? this question is the most direct, but it isn't as simple as it sounds. for example, you might desire therapy and know that therapists cost a rate of, say $60-250 an hour in your town. what if no therapist in your local beloved community speaks your mother language? what is the honest price tag for your therapy sessions if you have to travel three hours to see a therapist who shares your cultural, linguistic, ancestral perspective? #jajaja.

decolonial bizness world is a free and open method for business education that promotes reparations and decolonization. #reparations means repairing the damage del #racismo, #capitalismo, and settler #colonialismo.
name: darshan elena campos

text:
i wrote this song in the aftermath of the kavanaugh/ford case.  i felt like once the verdict was reached everyone expected survivors to shut up about it. to shut up about our stories, to shut up about our truths.  we spent weeks reliving our trauma. i met with friends to check in on our mental states, to make sure we were all doing ok. we heard things from people we thought loved us that proved we could never share our story with them.  though i’m not comfortable sharing the details of what i’ve been through personally with everyone, i know how important it is to keep talking about. to keep the conversation going. to continue letting others know they are heard and they are not alone.  to use our voices to continue to educate and prove that this is not ok.  in the production of this song i found myself scared to speak up. i had an artistic vision.  i knew what i wanted but i didn’t know how to stand up for myself. i realized there was a time and a person in my life that made me feel like the only way i could exist was by keeping myself small. staying out of the way. not drawing too much attention to myself.  doing what everyone else wanted, at the sacrifice of my own personal needs.  this song opened my eyes to that and allowed me to take the steps to begin to heal.  i learned how to express my vision, to work together with the gentlemen that built this project with me. to speak my truth. i’m still finding my voice. but i’m proud to say i spoke up for this project and i am so so proud of how it turned out.  whatever you’re going through, whatever your personal battles are, whatever cage you find yourself in, i hope you never lose your voice.  your voice matters. your story matters. you matter. never forget that.  in sharing our stories, in working together, by opening our hearts and minds, we can make big changes for the better. 
song of the caged bird-by kayla hawkins 
available to download/stream nov 16th

tweet_full:
i wrote this song in the aftermath of the kavanaugh/ford case.  i felt like once the verdict was reached everyone expected survivors to shut up about it. to shut up about our stories, to shut up about our truths.  we spent weeks reliving our trauma. i met with friends to check in on our mental states, to make sure we were all doing ok. we heard things from people we thought loved us that proved we could never share our story with them.  though i’m not comfortable sharing the details of what i’ve been through personally with everyone, i know how important it is to keep talking about. to keep the conversation going. to continue letting others know they are heard and they are not alone.  to use our voices to continue to educate and prove that this is not ok.  in the production of this song i found myself scared to speak up. i had an artistic vision.  i knew what i wanted but i didn’t know how to stand up for myself. i realized there was a time and a person in my life that made me feel like the only way i could exist was by keeping myself small. staying out of the way. not drawing too much attention to myself.  doing what everyone else wanted, at the sacrifice of my own personal needs.  this song opened my eyes to that and allowed me to take the steps to begin to heal.  i learned how to express my vision, to work together with the gentlemen that built this project with me. to speak my truth. i’m still finding my voice. but i’m proud to say i spoke up for this project and i am so so proud of how it turned out.  whatever you’re going through, whatever your personal battles are, whatever cage you find yourself in, i hope you never lose your voice.  your voice matters. your story matters. you matter. never forget that.  in sharing our stories, in working together, by opening our hearts and minds, we can make big changes for the better. 
song of the caged bird-by kayla hawkins 
available to download/stream nov 16th

text_retweet:
#repost @metoo_in
• • • • •
at the very start of my career, i was shooting a telefilm in kodaikanal. i was the lead. and very excited. alok nath was my on-screen father and reema lagoo my mother.
alok nath was very impressed with me and called me "god's own child" and openly praised me every day. i was over the moon. i was a huge fan of this wonderful babuji.. i felt so fortunate happy and confident.
till one night after an early pack up. the cast went out for dinner. at dinner he got progressively drunk and started insisting i sit with him and that i belonged to him and other stuff that i don't clearly remember but it made me very nervous and uncomfortable. my co-star realised what was happening and got me out of there.
we went back to the hotel without dinner. it was late and i was back in my room and the costume dada came to my room to give me my clothes for the next day as i had a very early call time. few minutes after he left there was a knock on my door i opened the door thinking it was him again .. it was an inebriated alok nath i instinctively tried to shut the door but he pushed it and lunged at me, i stepped aside he went flying past me into the room .. i fell back toward the bathroom door he lunged at me again screaming i want you you're mine .. i dodged again he went into the bathroom and i think i latched the loo door and ran out of my room down the corridor into the lobby. fortunately, my dop was there making a call from the reception ..
he came back to my room what ensued was traumatic because a belligerent alok nath refused to leave.. kept screaming shouting threatening abusing trying to grab me.. but at some point we managed to make him leave. the hairdresser was called and made to sleep in my room i was so shaken up.
in a few hours i had scenes with bauji, in one i had to sit on his lap and cry. i still feel nauseous when i think of it.

#metoo #metoomovement #metooindia #aloknath #therapeworkshop #rape #bollywood #celeb #celebrities #womaninred

text:
(link in bio)

this saturday november 17 2018

this year will mark the 3rd year of paint your truth. paint your truth is a painting event for sexual assault survivors in the massachusetts area. all materials are free and survivors get to take their art projects home. we celebrate, support and paint in  the most authentic and carefree way. the purpose of paint your truth is to encourage survivors to continue or start their healing journey after they’ve attended paint your truth. "it is imperative that these acts of wrongdoings do not continue unchecked for it is our children who pay the highest cost." - author vie ciné

text:
"if (you think) you're not part of the problem, be part of the solution."
.
met die gedachte loop ik al ruim een jaar rond nadat ik voor mijn neus geconfronteerd werd met onacceptabel gedrag door een man tegen een vrouw. geweld tegen vrouwen begint bij mannen. laten we dan ook zorgen dat het bij ons eindigt. daarom zet ik mij in tegen geweld tegen vrouwen.
.
het leverde mij een uitnodiging op voor een weekend met medestrijders en rolmodellen, op initiatief van @emancipator.nl over mannelijkheid, vrouwelijkheid en over geweld tegen vrouwen.
.
and what an epic experience it was! 2 dagen lang gender mythes doorprikken, mezelf en anderen kennen en vooral met prachtige mensen zijn. mensen waar ik ontzettend veel respect en liefde voor heb, ook al ken ik ze net. samen zijn wij de eerste golf van de steen in het water. doe jij mee?
.
oh ja, die gedachte die al een jaar in mijn hoofd zit? dat wordt langzaam maar zeker een concreet initiatief. en daar zal ik je binnenkort meer over vertellen!
.
#genderequality #feminism #emancipation #maleemancipation #femaleemancipation #domesticviolence #violenceagainstwomen #metoo #whiteribbon #womensrights #standup #speakout #queensonsneakers

text:
low mood, depression, anxiety and even autism are associated with altered serotonin levels. given that our gut is the primary site of serotonin production, the gut-derived serotonin has an impact on mental wellbeing, imperative to feeling a sense of calm, contentment and peace.  the role that gut bacteria plays in regulating serotonin production must be nurtured. !avoid!: processed foods, refinded sugar, msg, limit caffeine, limit gluten to once or twice a week, meat, dairy, nicotine, limit alcohol intake to once or twice a week. --- ways to start improving your gut health -- eat more vegetables and fruit for the healing and liver health.

focus on fibre.

eat plenty of prebiotic-rich foods. fermented foods/inulin

eat more probiotic-rich foods/supplements 
drink water

reduce junk food intake

text:
maybe a bit intense for a monday morning but no book has ever hit me like this one. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
i was sexually assaulted as a young teen by an adult who was supposed to help me, not hurt me, and these feelings were ones i shared, not at first, but eventually. it took a couple years, but then over a short time, i too began to build my fortress. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
it took me years to understand what happened, why i took on that blame and shame, and, although my wall of safety was never that big, it took me many more years to begin to feel safe enough to tear that wall down. and some days with everyone sharing, as glad as i am to have so many people putting it out there and having truths heard, it pulls the scab off the wound and starts the healing process all over again. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
if you haven’t read hunger, please know that it may be a trigger for those of you dealing with sexual assault, but it may also be worth reading. i know it has been for me. 🖤

text: my son is an eagle scout 🦅. during his time in scouts, i was the rank advancement chair.  the boys would meet with myself and other parents for  their board of reviews to demonstrate they were ready for their advancement to the next rank. one question regularly asked was what good turn had the scout done that day.  a “good turn” is doing something for someone because you see and know it is helpful to that person - without boasting about it.  it demonstrates kindness and building of character.  today’s monday challenge is to do a good turn 💜

text:
【オンラインサロンのリニューアルオープンについてお知らせ】
.
今日はオンラインサロンについて大切なお知らせがあります。
.
すでにご存知の方もいらっしゃるかもしれませんがサロン運営に利用しているgoogle＋が来年の8月をもって閉鎖されることになりました。
.
それに伴い、新しく「band(バンド)」というアプリを利用してサロンを12月からリニューアルする予定です。
.
.
「band」では自助グループのスケジュール確認や、現在その都度メールでお知らせいただいている出欠のご連絡もアプリ内から簡単にしていただくことができます。アプリの仕様も明るい印象で現在よりも快適に楽しくご利用いただけるのではないかなと思っています。
.
.
ただ、一点大きな変更点があり、アプリの仕様の関係で自分を大切にするためのプログラム「tsumiki」をサロン上に掲載しておくことが難しくなり、tsumikiのサロン公開を終了する予定でおります。
.
.
それに伴い下記の形での価格改定を行います。
.
.
①オンラインサロンご入会金
3.000円→1.000円(自助グループで直接お会いできる場合500円)
.
②tsumikiメール販売　2.000円→2.000円(改定なし)
.
③tsumiki book　2.500円
（現在準備中、tsumikiを冊子にする予定です)
.
④tsumikiメール販売をご利用いただいた方サロンのご入会金1.000円off→リニューアルに伴い終了
.
.
.
これまでオンラインサロンのご入会金はtsumikiの公開に加え活動費としてのご協力をいただくかたちで3.000円と設定しておりました。
.
また、わたし自身の気持ちとして自分の経験を生かした仕事をしたいという思いからこの活動に仕事という側面を持たせるためこのような価格設定をとっていましたが、活動を続ける中で心境の変化もあり、ネット上だけでの繋がりとなることから安全性の確保という意味で有料であることに変わりはありませんが今後はできるだけご負担の少ない形で運営できればと思っています。
.
.
.
これからも自分に向き合うセルフケアの場としてmintを精一杯運営していきますので、今後ともどうぞよろしくお願いいたします。
.
リニューアルオープンの準備が整い次第、また改めてお知らせいたします。
.
リニューアルに関して何かご不明な点などございましたらお気軽にお問い合わせください。
selfhelpgroup.mint@gmail.com
.
self help group「mint」
野間千華子
.
.
.

text: representing awe, co-founder @karenbate_kbconcepts had the honor to meet prince william county delegate jennifer carroll-foy sunday. jennifer is one of the awesome women leading the @ratifyera2018 effort to have virginia be the 38th (and final) state needed to ratify the equal rights amendment - and make history! did you know the word “woman” is not in the us constitution and we do not have equal rights under the law? as jennifer, a graduate of @virginia_military_institute, says: we are tired of asking permission and tired of being told no. era now! she will introduce the resolution in the virginia general assembly on january 9th. and like so many other things in the last year - #metoo, #timesup and the #pinkwave, elected leaders who’ve voted no year after year against equal rights for women will think twice this time - because our time is now: ratify era va! jennifer has graciously agreed to speak at an awe meeting early next year so stay tuned for more news about that too! #ratifyera #varatifyera #equalrights #era #beawesome #jennifercarrollfoy

text:
god things take time; right time for birth and another for death, a right time to plant and another to reap, a right time to kill and another to heal, a right time to destroy and another to construct, a right time to cry and another to laugh, a right time to lament and another to cheer, a right time to make love and another to abstain, a right time to embrace and another to part, a right time to search and another to count your losses, a right time to hold on and another to let go, a right time to rip out and another to mend, a right time to shut up and another to speak up, a right time to love and another to hate, a right time to wage war and another to make peace.
ecclesiastes 3:2‭-‬8 msg

text:
*
**this moment**
*
************ *
we only have 
this one moment
from which to define
our humanity
caring and benevolent
careless and tyrannical
there is no in between 
an epidemic of brutality
a wave of compassion
the first is seemingly common
the later a vanishing parallel
misogynistic behavior 
celebrated in elections
noble people 
with noble intent 
vilified in the public eye
the media partially to blame
our political climate 
mostly to blame
#metoo now a tool
to disgrace the innocent
how do we recover
our lost humanity
in this vanishing moment?

text:
much love to @adriennemareebrown for bringing it home at facingrace this past week. 
our work is to keep at it, in all the different ways we can offer our energy, resources & skills, to celebrate each victory, to wage joy amidst struggle, and to never forget that the world we are working toward is radically more beautiful than anything we can currently touch. “we have to win as much as we can, but never forget that the whole game is rigged. we can’t confuse winning in the current paradigm as the same as liberation. our work is to persuade the world of a world that has not yet been.” amb, thank you. 
#emergentstrategy #liberation

text:
var är bonnie säger jag, då drar hon täcket över huvet, lägger sig under och ler. 
hon vet ingenting om oron jag känner och alla framtida faror jag ser.
i helgen läste vi om två unga män som bestämt sig för att mörda. en kvinna valdes slumpmässigt ut och hon kommer aldrig mer vakna en lörda. ”slumpmässigt” så våldtogs hon först och knivhöggs sen till döds i en främlings lägenhet. vad hennes sista fasansfulla tankar var är det ingen som säkert vet. varför jag, vilka är ni? vad har jag gjort? och vad kommer ni göra? för varje våldtagen och mördad kvinna står åter tusen med tilliten och tryggheten förstörda! 
män som misshandlar, våldtar och mördar kvinnor är det största hotet mot jämställdhet vi har. att 300 män under 2000-talet har mördat 300 kvinnor i nära relationer måste tas på fullaste allvar. vad är en beslutsfattande och makthavande position värd. om ditt handlingsutrymme är begränsat och din frihet undernärd? ni män som känner er hotade av alla miljoner röster under #metoo och dom som fortfarande samlar kraft i tystnad. alla dom kvinnorna är fortfarande ett mindre hot mot samhället än dom män som mördar och misshandlar av sårat ego och hämndlystnad. så många tankar och livet med bonnie blir en smärtsam lupp.titt ut hör jag mig själv säga och samtidigt skriker hjärtat -se upp! 
#pappapoesi

text:
over a year ago, the #metoo movement took off on twitter, encouraging women all over the world to voice their stories of sexual assault and abuse, and call out their abusers. here, we take a look at some of the women who have been crucial to this movement.

tarana burke, founder of the #metoo movement 
as an activist, tarana burke often spent time with children of colour at youth camps. at one such camp, she met a young girl who confided in her about her stepfather sexually abusing her. burke could barely make it through five minutes of the conversation, and abruptly cut the young girl off, directing her to another counsellor. she was ridden with guilt as the child walked away from her because she could not bring herself to tell the young girl that she understood her pain. she could not find the courage to say, “me too”. the #metoo movement began in 2006 when burke, along with other activists, founded just be inc., a youth organisation to guide young women of colour in their process of self-discovery and ultimately towards empowerment. following this, they put up a myspace page that was very well-received by many young survivors of sexual abuse. .
.
.

text:
machi francisca linconao es defensora de los derechos humanos y autoridad espiritual indígena del pueblo mapuche en chile. machi francisca linconao trabaja por la protección de los derechos del pueblo mapuche y la preservación de sus territorios ancestrales. en 2008, la defensora indígena presentó un recurso de protección ante la corte suprema de chile con el objetivo de impedir la tala ilegal en los bosques chilenos que amenazaba la siembra de las plantas medicinales utilizadas por el pueblo mapuche. machi francisca linconao fue la primera líder indígena en denunciar, ante tribunales chilenos, las violaciones al convenio 169 de la organización internacional del trabajo sobre pueblos indígenas y tribales, logrando implementar la protección a los derechos de los pueblos indígenas desde la perspectiva derecho internacional de los derechos humanos.
perseguida por los poderes políticos y económicos del estado de chile, por su condición de mujer pobre, indígena y además sabia.
.
.
.
.

text:
今日のスケジュール
裁判所→警視庁本部捜査2課→裁判所
正直、文書受付とか言うけど裁判所の記録の転記を事実として認めないってどうよ？
別の捜査2課の方がお役所仕事ですみませんって謝ってくれたから少し怒りが収まったけどさ。
とにかく、警察が事実認定しない事多い。
結局、被害者が金払って証拠資料集めてるけど集めてる資料内容が警視庁が逮捕した案件の報道記事が大半なんだよね。
伊藤詩織さんのレイプ事件や電通の自殺した高橋まつりさんの業務上過失致死罪が認められなかった件とか未成年の女の子に対する痴漢やレイプ事件の大半は立証困難&証拠不十分でサイコパス犯罪者が野放しにされてる日本。
コレ、まずいでしょ？
暴力団の癒着事件は必ず刑事告訴する。

桜田門にて。

#metoo 
#metoomovement

text: my horrible childhood set the course for my adulthood. i refused to stay in the position of victim so i broke the cycle of abuse and became a survivor. it was the hardest thing i ever did. i refused to be another statistic so i started getting professional help to start the healing process from the childhood that gave me the diagnosis of ptsd. i read somewhere how children that grow up in abusive homes struggle with school. i'm proud to say that for me this is not the case. i'm in every single honor society my school offers, by the end of this semester i will be on the president's list. my gpa is currently a 4.0.  i'm not responsible for what happened to me however i'm responsible for my own healing and what i do next. 💜💙💜💙💜💙💜💙💜💙

text:
that’s when the regret sets in.
*
all the things you would’ve done, you should’ve done, you could’ve done haunt you. it’s behind you now and you can’t help but think about the opportunities you missed that could have made all the difference.
*
but those regrettable events shaped you. they taught you lessons. they opened your eyes to what’s true and what isn’t. they were a part of his plan and they groomed you for his blessings.
*
i can’t go back. even if i could, it wasn’t meant to be fixed. none of this time was wasted, and i know i’ll make you proud...🙏🏽

text:
who knew that there were so many ways to bring my words to life!🤩😂🤣 •
i thought this random music app would be a great way to introduce a new concept of my writing to you guys!😃 as my journey has unfolded, and my writing has evolved, i have been going in a different direction writing-wise for the last month or so...and have been songwriting. i am absolutely tone deaf though, and couldn’t sing a tune to save my life....so i’m on the lookout for a songstress who can bring my words to life! i am going to be picky with who i choose to sing my songs, as i would want someone who has travelled our path and can bring their real emotions into my songs. 👌✌️ •
please pm me if you or someone you know would be interested in collaborating on this project with me. i am slowly venturing out in the open with all that i am and all that i have to offer, and i’m ready to start taking some real steps outside of my comfortzone. i am quietly looking at other avenues at the moment, but thought it wouldn’t hurt to cast the net out here with you guys too. and just so yas know....you heard it hear first yo!!! i haven’t officially started turning the wheels on this yet, so chatting to you guys first is my way of testing the waters i guess...lol #watchthisspace #cptsd #domesticviolence #healingjourney #survivor #thriver #faithbasedsupport #writingforacause #sharingourstory #raisingawareness 🗣 #poetry #songwriting #singerwanted #collaboration #metoo #whiteribbon #goldcoast #australia #auckland #nz

text:
for the record, #ponce is not #aguadilla or even close to it. it is however a useful spot for mi proyecto #decolonialbiznessworld given the joint “civil-military airport.” btw there is nothing #civil about the #military. #fucktheusmilitary. 
#guayama is, of course, not near ponce or aguadilla, and that’s where i’ll head in time. it is also #3 hours away. for now, i’ll learn this land as she and mis #zemis want to teach me. it is called #sanaciónespiritual and #initiation. 
don’t #trust my #abuela, mi granny #muerta, who was raped at 12 and bore her first child at 13. that child was adopted by a rich family. who was the rapist? where is my stolen auntie? she’s stolen because we’ve been denied each other and yet also forced together by the violence of racism, capitalism, and #settlercolonialism. 
slavery is a forced breeding program, so too prisons and the #prisonindustrialcomplex. rape is the #system of slavery. people are made by rape, and rape produces traumatized people. rapists are people or are they ghuls? 
don’t trust me either. #believe. or not.
i love that i’m in aguadilla. there’s a reason i’m here now. my #dreams were so #sweet and #fierce and #essential. 
i knew i *could* have researched the airports and blah blah blah. i figured aguadilla was near ponce or near enough that i’d learn a lot of #value. plus i heard and felt the #clarion call to come here to borikén quick. that’s why the “internet” kept sending me results for here, not ponce. so here i am, and i accept the beautiful challenge and initiation my dead granny just ensured for me.
and i knew that i could come here or not. the ticket to aguadilla from stl was priced right for a woman whose been the #target of hackers, which has allowed her — i mean me and #metoo — to finally get out of stl despite ongoing backing issues and reach my sacred calling. #fuckmoney. #fuckbanks. #fuckgoogle. #googleprotectssexualpredators.

he/she touched me. but i could not do anything.

often when people are faced into situations where they are being groped, they panic and don't raise their voices out. but what can you do when situations like this do arise?

if you are in a crowded place, shout at the person, tell people around you that you have been touched inappropriatly by that person.

always speak out when this happens , tell your friends or family about the incident and most importantly, be aware and speak out!

let us stand together to combat this issue!

text:
что же было дальше...?🤓
а дальше, как это обычно бывает я влипла, вляпалась, да нет же!....как его? влюбилась!😻😸
хоть мой внутренний голос при первом взгляде на него прокричал мне: «беги!»
я его не послушалась🤷🏻‍♀️ и....полетела карусель звонков и смсок, 
ночных свиданий у подруги и кафе эспресcо 
и сцены ревности, скандалы, знание подруги, 
и так по замкнутому кругу...........🤦🏻‍♀️
в общем это они самые👏🏻 незрелые и токсичные отношения💔 куда ж без них родимых нынче-то, а?)))
хотя начиналось всё красиво💑 
как в кино💖 а вот заканчивалось тоже, как в кино...только не романтическом, а как в триллере...типа пилы👻
но сначала о хорошем, да?😉
это был 2011, я была влюблена, казалось, что счастлива, училась-работала, ела фактически всё подряд - скажу честно😸
в общем обычная жизнь😜
я даже не пп-шничала особо-то, просто...жила😇
...продолжение следует...

text:
🎯
📢лондон – буюк британиянинг “artreview” журнали санъат оламидаги энг нуфузли одамлар рўйхатини эълон қилди. ҳар йили аниқланадиган “power 100” рейтингига галеристлар, рассомлар, дизайнерлар ва турли ижтимоий ҳаракатлар киритилган. рўйхатнинг тўлиқ шакли “artreview.com” нашрида эълон қилинди.

рўйхатни германиялик девид цвернер исмли арт-дилер бошлаб беради. унинг нью-йорк, лондон ва гонконг шаҳарларида шахсий галереялари бор. ўтган йили цвернер ушбу рейтингда 5-ўринни эгаллаган.

америкалик рассом керри жеймс “power 100” рўйхатининг 2-ўрнидан жой олган. ушбу рассомнинг “past times (1997)” деб номланган картинаси аукционда 21,1 млн долларга сотилган. бу нарх ким ошди савдосида картина учун тўланган нарх сифатида рекорд ўрнатган. ушбу савдо рассомни “power 100” рейтингидаги 68-ўриндан 2-ўринга кўтарди.

учинчи ўрин #metoo ижтимоий ҳаракатга насиб қилди. ушбу ҳаракат санъат соҳасида гендер муносабатларда учрайдиган муаммолар бўйича турли лойиҳаларни йўлга қўйган.

шунингдек, рассом ай вейвей, “serpentine” галереясининг раҳбари ханс-ульрих обрист, фотограф нан голдин ва вольфганг тильманс, япониялик мусаввир яёи кусама, тейт галереяси раҳбари мария белшоу, “fondazione prada” мода уйининг дизайнери миучча прада каби санъат соҳасининг турли вакиллари “power 100” рўйхатига киритилган. #turon24 #tashkent #bizturon24  #uzb #uzbekistan
name: Uzbek

text:
e bildiğin ellediler beni yav, yeminle, hemi de kıçımdan... #metoo 😨

kirlilerimizi çamaşır yıkamaya vermiştik, otelde de bu hizmet var ama 1 kilosu 1 usd. ben ara sokakların birinde 1 kilosu 50cent.e bulmuştum oraya verdim. neyse uzatmayayım, biraz kenarda bi yer orası, azıcık yürüdüm temizlenmiş kıyafetleri almak için, 5 kilo çamaşır, koymuşlar koca bi çantaya, yüklendim dönüyorum, dönüşte de hemen her gün uğradığım, sokak yemekleri satan bi kadıncağız var, ondan da şimdi yazmayayım canınız çekmesin çok hoş yemekler, o da diğer elimde, az ileride bi süpermarket var oradan da 2 adet 1.5litrelik pet şişe su, anlayacağınız elim kolum hem ağır hem dolu. hadi diyorum, şu yemeklerin yanına, yine genelde aldığımız, yağda kızartılmış ekmekler var, o da güzel olur diyip dalıyorum pazara, işte ne olduysa o pazarda oluyor herşey... pazar dediysem tarihi bi yer, üstü kapalı, herkes üst üste, alt alta ve bi o kadar da dar ki anlatamam yani değil iki kolunu, tek kolunu açsan, sokaklar o kadarcık. elim kolum dolu, aman ona çarpmayayım, buna çarpmayayım, yok meyvelere vurup indirmeyeyim, millete dokunmayayım diye diye, bi öyle kıvır, bi böyle kıvır, öyle dön, böyle dön yürüyorum veee bi el hissettim sol popomda bi an, hemi de ne elleme, bildiğin avuçlama.  çok mu kıvırdım acep?...🤔 noluyo leeyn edasıyla bi döndüm, tam arkamda yığınla insan, hani kadını da var, erkeği de, kim elledi beni bilinmez, kızgın ve de bi o kadar asabi bi bakış fırlattım ortaya, herkes bi durdu o an, birkaçı ile gözgöze geldim, lakin bilemedim kim elledi beni, döndüm önüme tekrar söylene söylene, kös kös, bugün de yemeyi ver di mi yağda kızarmış ekmeği, boğaz yüzünden ellendik resmen... 😁

sol popom şu an biraz hüzünlü, içine kapanık, travma halinde, bi ilki yaşamanın verdiği derin bi şokta, ama neylersin ki hayat devam ediyor... 😆😎 yakında tekrar görüşmek üzere kendinize iyi bakın dostlar...

text:
| the best way to start the week 💜 gifts from @fatimaortega13 🎁| «monstruas y centauras», de marta sanz 📖.
.
sobre el libro: tres acontecimientos más una sentencia (el #metoo, la carta de las intelectuales francesas, la huelga feminista del 8 de marzo y la sentencia de la manada) han marcado la agenda en los últimos meses y han puesto en el punto de mira el concepto del feminismo hoy. marta sanz reflexiona acerca de lo que ello supone, cómo posicionarse ante esos hechos concretos, cómo «proteger» la lucha feminista de la simplificación y comercialización de un capitalismo que lo puede absorber todo, y piensa también sobre las cuotas y el poder, para llegar a la conclusión de que quizás lo que deba modificarse sea la noción de poder misma... una reflexión de una mujer que se pregunta, en sus actuaciones públicas y privadas, en cada gesto y cada palabra, cuál es el camino hacia la igualdad 💪🏼
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

امروز از حراست ورزشگاه تختی تهران با من تماس گرفتند و گفتند: خانم طباطبائی دیده شده شما روز چهارشنبه مصادف با وفات حضرت رسول (درود خداوند بر ایشان و خاندان مطهرش) در ورزشگاه به همراه آقایون دویدید. به گوش ما رسوندن و شما دیگه حق فعالیت در اینجا رو ندارید. 
گفتم: من تنها میدوام.
گفتند: دو و میدانی بانوان اینجا ممنوعه
و در نهایت هم ازشون تشکر کردم که تلفنی به اطلاع بنده رسوندن نه مثل سری پیش چند خانواده رو دم در مجموعه به صف نگه دارن و راه ندن.
آقایون محترم بفرمایید این مردونگی(نردونگی) چیه که ما بابت محروم بودن از این نعمت بزرگ حقوق فعالیتمون اینقدر محدوده.
تاسف برای کسانی که بنام دین و با دریافت پول مردم رو از ساده ترین حقوقشون منع میکنند.
ladies are not allowed to run in takhti stadium in iran.

text:
have you heard? “tootsie”, the 1980s movie starring dustin hoffman has been turned into a musical.
✨
with only a few previews in chicago under its corset, “tootsie” is apparently shaping up to be a hit.
✨
buzz was building during rehearsals for santino fontana, as the main character, and it seems to have exploded after his first performance in chicago recently. “i just saw next year’s tony-winning performance for best actor in a musical,” a high-powered broadway executive texted when the curtain came down.
✨
fontana plays the dustin hoffman role of michael dorsey, an actor so fussy and demanding, nobody will cast him. he transforms himself into dorothy michaels and becomes a star — and a better person.
✨
apparently the stage version retains “the bones” of the 1982 movie but has been completely rethought for the stage. the big change is the setting. the movie took place in the world of soap operas. the musical’s creators — composer david yazbek, writer robert horn and director scott ellis — have set their story on broadway, where dorothy becomes a musical-comedy sensation of bette midler-like fame. further, while the film had dorothy’s rise chronicled via magazine covers, accompanied by the lyrics “go, tootsie, go!,” the musical shows her name appearing on one broadway marquee after another. michael’s love interest still throws a martini in michael’s face, but the musical has eliminated her father who unwittingly falls in love with dorothy. in the stage adaptation, her admirer is now the male lead in the show within the show. dorothy’s director in the musical is modeled on dabney coleman’s sexist soap director. the character is still said to be arrogant but, in these #metoo times, no longer a predator.
✨
oh me oh my! it sounds fabulous! and it’s also refreshing to know that they have updated the story to suit present times. “tootsie” opened on 30 september 2018 in chicago. previews begin on 29 march 2019 in new york at the marquis theatre.
wish i could go to the “tootsie” box office!

text:
nowdays i am learning difference 
between words which rhyme
or 
pronounced similiar
or 
have similiar meanings
like-
sympathy and empathy.
i like how one has negative shade
and other perhaps,
represents the purest feelings of all. 
empathy is difficult to offer. 
while sympathy is served on plate. 
so when i was molested at nine. 
and confessed 10 years later
i was invited to this huge feast
where sympathy was served on huge plates. 
i felt constipated
these were saltless dishes,
they had no taste. 
they were just served for sake of it. 
the congregation was full of mighty people. 
my classmates whom i tried to evesdrop
perhaps they said-' it happened years ago'. i felt exhausted. 
i found a nearby park. 
sat down. 
i felt a pat on my back. 
it was leo, a stray cat,
whom i feed everyday. 
i patted her head. 
she spoke in language of empathy. 
which is different from clutter of sympathy
- you can not understand the empathatic words many times yet they have a magical and soothing touch.
