text:
yoga;
⠀
i don't post as much as i used to about my yoga practice or my teaching, or rather, i dont post about it at all, but it is still a part of my practice, it has just evolved.
⠀
i believe all practicing should be evolving. practice is personal and it requires active participation from the student. as the student develops greater awareness of their body they are able to adapt and figure out what is the best way for them to get the most out of their practice.
⠀
i believe there are a lot of misconceptions about what is and isn't yoga and it is a sure fact that there are an innumerable number of misconceptions about the body and what is beneficial or potentially harmful.
⠀
there are misconceptions of what it means to strengthen and what it takes to develop true improvements in range of motion.
⠀
there are misconceptions about what it means to be a teacher and what it means to have a practice.
⠀
that doesn't mean that i think i have the answers. i don't think my style is better than anyone else. it's just my style. i developed it based on my experience with strength, movement and mobility practice and how i could best integrate that information into a vinyasa-ish class.
⠀
my goal is simply to make the box bigger and expand what it is that people think of as yoga.
⠀
because at the end of the day, in my opinion, your yoga is your practice. shapes on a mat are shapes on a mat. how you approach the process of creating those shapes is yoga. and not to mention all the other yoga(practice) you do throughout the day; how you speak. how you act. what you eat. how you breath. what you expose yourself to; it's all making you who you are. (your yoga is whether you are consciously engaged in those experiences or not, or how mindful your are of your level of participation)
⠀
so really you don't have to call it yoga. you could just call it practice. or life.
⠀
my life is what i make it because of what i choose to spend my time doing or not doing, and how i go about the process of doing or not doing.
⠀
🐈 📿 mala, in the background giving me support. she knows whatsup.
⠀
#yoga #lululemon #yogaeverydamnday #namaste

text:
do you know someone who frequently demeans you? someone who is bitterly jealous of literally everything and needs constant praise? someone whose insatiable arrogance means they blindly believe their own superiority and that the input of others in society is irrelevant and inferior? that those around them, or even the whole world, truly *needs* their facilitation? 
_
welcome to narcissistic personality disorder 101, with dr jo! narcissists are stalkers on a never-ending hunt for people or situations to exploit and dominate. hugely delusional, these perverse individuals are in constant search of power, reverence and control. they are manipulators, psychological torturers - twisted and corrupt - who literally thrive on the ‘power’ of driving wedges between friends, marriages, communities, or even entire races and religions. 
_
i recently had an experience with one of these devious and delusional people, which led me to think about this heinous disorder in a broader, global context. drum roll please: president trump *has* narcissistic personality disorder. he is a walking, talking, tweeting case study - and thanks to the us republican party and the (approx) 25% of americans who voted for him, the world now unfortunately has front row seats to continually witness this intensely calculating personality disorder.
_
knowing how narcissism has besieged humanity throughout history means that i, for one, cannot just watch these deadly delusions be repeated, as trump continues to marginalise, rationalise and dehumanise.
_
please take the time to be conscious about current affairs and read as much about it as possible. if you would like to read my scribblings on the matter, it's currently penned in a piece called ‘pathological narcissism in politics’, which is on my website and currently linked from my bio. it’s not light-hearted, yet i hope you can all take the time to read it and think about the concept within the context of our current political climate.
_
this piece is dedicated to anyone who feels marginalised and oppressed; to everyone whose people have been persecuted in history; and to every single person who has been viciously attacked by a pathological narcissist.

text:
and so on and so on, in every area of their lives. see, narcissists are never satisfied. that’s a huge part of the problem. they are perpetually bored. they are constantly chasing a need to have the best, the most, to find the “thing” that will finally validate them and make them feel worthy and whole.
.
but that “thing” does not exist. that thing is a wound inside them they need to heal but refuse to acknowledge. this constant craving is one of the saddest things about narcissism. a narcissist will spend their lifetime yearning for something impossible to achieve, they’ll destroy a number of innocent lives trying to achieve it, and in the end they never find what they’re looking for.
.
because that’s what happens when you search for validation from the outside and not from within. you never feel fully satisfied. you’re the only thing that can fill you up. 💛🦋

text:
nani maa never allowed me to pluck any of the flowers from the balcony. she had made her mini garden and it included all the beautiful ones liles, roses, cherry blossom, mogra etc. she would wait to the flowers to fall off on its own and used them to make itar from it.
.
"why you don't simply pluck it?"
i questioned.
.
"the smell won't be that alluring." she smiled.
.
"what's the logic?" i shooted.
.
"love." she replied calmy.

i settled for her answer but was still confused. but i knew nani maa loved gardening and she would take care of each bud like her own child. which included timely watering, cutting the dead leaves and also assuring they get proper sunlight. i started believing that it was her love and affection which made the itar smell like hevean.

i grew young and so my love for nature and flowers. i had grown my own garden in the veranda. and i nurtured them like nani used to. however i never made itar out of the fallen ones. i used them as bookmarks.
.
"they will die anyway yet you love them?"
she asked me at the dinner table when i cooked our favourite dish. after i moved to the new city for studies i met this girl named swati. she was healthy, fair and cute and i loved her like i loved flowers.
.
"even humans die, still we love them." i replied.

later, on her birthday i gifted her 'itar' which i made from the fallen flowers in my veranda.
.
"how does this smells so amazing what it is made up of?" she questioned while still inhaling the scent from her wrist.
.
"love." i replied.
.
.
darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.
.

text:
i decided that for 2018 no matter what came my way i’d choose faith over fear. i even received this necklace as a gift to serve as a reminder of this intentional choice.•
•
after an incredible year of super high highs and super low lows... here are my choices: 
glass half empty; it was as if i had beckoned the immediate curse to hit my life and the universe offered opportunity after opportunity to practice what i had promised. 
glass half full; this was a game changing event that has brought me nothing but incredible gifts of light and love. 
reality: it’s a little of it all.•
•
life is full of love and people who love and opportunities to practice giving and receiving love. and also... sometimes that’s a really hard thing to do. 
anger and rage are definitely two emotions i have uncomfortably felt through the last several months. unlike anything i’ve felt before or want to feel again.•
•
but my faith is consistent. 
as quickly as i forget i surrender. 
as often as i ask i give. 
i remain open to possibilities, adventures and forgiveness through out and because i manifest them, that’s what i receive .•
•
it’s ok to feel both sadness and joy simultaneously. 
it’s ok to forgive someone and then the next day wake up angry and forgive them again. 
and now i know, so i don’t have to be perfectly put together anymore.•
•
•
•
#itsoktonotbeok 
#madeformore
#youareenough
#iamenough

text:
“the shadow marnies & marnie” curtain call/rappel 👏, #metopera the shadow marnies [l to r]: @deanna.breiwick, @disellalar, @brrrring (rebecca ringle kamarei), & #peabodysouthwell . marnie:  @isabelleonardny. this sumptuous production was flawless in its adaptation & rendering of a perfect mid-century noirish vibe. i’m cinematic by nature & i was drawn in to the point i didn’t want it to end. @nicomuhly’s opera creates a palpable tension where the multiplex music itself serves as a character, which some critics may have missed. our glimpse into the 1959 past of course allows an examination of our current gendered milieu, but in my warped mind i could help but think of an operatic  #metoo trilogy with valerie solanas (i shot andy warhol) & hayley stark (hard candy). kudos to @metopera, as i loved this as well as the spring reimagining of così set in #brooklyn.

costume designer: @ariannephillips
conductor: #robertspano

text:
after recent events involving a double rib dislocation.... i’ve realized a few things about gaining strength.

a couple years ago, when i was at my smallest, i was very weak. most of the “weight loss” was in fact muscle loss. i had no strength, was constantly fatigued and couldn’t protect myself.  i was assaulted that same year....i couldn’t even push him off. after everything that happened.... i vowed that a man would never push me around and physically hurt me again. even though i wasn’t ready to change my disordered eating... i knew i needed to change. 
fast forward 4 years..... despite not being able to stop the dislocations from happening during a wrestling match.... i was able to defend myself and shove the other person off with my muscles. 
men against women is never a fair fight. it is not okay for them to push you around. to use their weight to pin you down.  it’s time to fight back and protect ourselves, for ourselves, by ourselves. 
here is to women, having the strength to protect and fight. to be safe. to have confidence in our bodies and what it is capable of.  #fuckabuse #fuckmen #womenempowerment #bestrong #protectyourself #fightforyourself #healthylifestyle #doitforyou #metoo

text:
when we understand the character of god, when we grasp something of his holiness, then we begin to understand the radical character of our sin and hopelessness. helpless sinners can survive only by grace. our strength is futile in itself; we are spiritually impotent without the assistance of a merciful god. we may dislike giving our attention to god's wrath and justice, but until we incline ourselves to these aspects of god's nature, we will never appreciate what has been wrought for us by grace. even edwards's sermon on sinners in god's hands was not designed to stress the flames of hell. the resounding accent falls not on the fiery pit but on the hands of the god who holds us and rescues us from it. the hands of god are gracious hands. they alone have the power to rescue us from certain destruction.
r.c. sproul

text:
revelation | @bea.santiago : sexual harassment is real. not just in pageants but everywhere!

i was molested when i was a child by a priest. he is still preaching somewhere in masbate.

i was told “why are you born too late! or sus sayang ka bea, kong napanganak ka lang mas maaga” by a pageant guy winner. i was 12years old and he was 21.

i was once touched inappropriately by a well known businessman. this guy is a well known ceo of a big company (companies pa nga e) he even organized parties for girls who didnt win with his friends🤮 (i think “hoping” they stopped it)

the next time i met him i was a candidate and the organizers were there to see things thoroughly.
he couldn’t interact with us because the chairwoman was present and so as the chaperones. - still he was talking nonsense to us 🙄 - we were at the congress or senate? when a queen was touched (her behind) while taking a photo. she immediately told me (with a help me look) so i put my hand covering her back protecting her from the “old well known perv” we just won an international pageant but still 😔 - i was working when i posed with a middle aged man (i had a feeling he was a perv) so i put both my hands behind me. he still managed to “accidentally swing her hand touching my behind”

it happens. no matter how careful you are. no matter how big/ popular/ old/ “religious” a person is, he can still be a pervert. 
i still feel guilty for not speaking up and file complaints or slap the hell out of them.  i guess speaking up now will help the future queens. - i am honestly really scared to speak up. i hope i wont regret this.

#missinternational2013 #missinternational #beasantiago #bbpilipinas #sexualharassment #metoo #pageanthology101 #pageantpresssociety

#repost @inkzonepoe with @get_repost
・・・
my whole life has been altered by a plethora of issues growing up - so i want to begin to make a difference in these areas through tattoos by either donating a portion of the funds, elevating spirits through my art or developing small art workshops on my own- anyone interested in getting tattoos that may relate to these causes... read on: - i’m  permanently offering specials in cancer ribbon tattoos & semi colon tattoos - 1.) the cancer ribbon tattoos will range $40-60 depending on size- half of which will be donated to a childhood cancer organization i follow on here - i take walk ins on certain days& evenings (hmu first to make sure i’m around) or if wanting to reserve a time i’ll require $20 deposit which can be sent directly to my paypal, cashapp or can be sent directly to the charity i’m donating to and you could just screenshot me the donation. 
2.) the semi colon tattoo will range between $20-40 depending on style & size (i have a few examples here ) my donation in return which i’m still trying to do, is offer a free coverup once a month to someone’s scars from self harm or a breast cancer survivor whose undergone a mastectomy (if your someone ready for this dm me) 
3.) i’m offering #metoo movement tattoos in support of domestic&sexual assault survivors for $40- i intend to continue to create art in this area for social awareness to make a difference ❤️
4.) last but not least - tattoos for coexisting - these tattoos will range $60-$100 depending on size (swipe to end) a portion of this i’ll be using for art supplies and offering once or twice a month free art classes or group art projects to those who are under daca/refugee status and /or are in lower socio economic neighbourhoods.  i intend to make a difference through my art however possible even though i’m barely getting by myself because it gives people hope just like it gave to me . i finally reached an advisor yesterday and i’ll slowly be building a website which will make things much more organized . but until then - if anyone is interested in any of these concepts while i slowly trust the process of transitioning to a professional artist 👩🏻‍🎨... feel fre

text: in regards to veterans day. glad you made it home. returning from war is to a degree the equivalent of returning from a hostile, from a jail. to agree to remove priveledges, for the betterment of the community. rather than having them removed so young, for being born a certain color or gender, ect. public service is important, it's something that with all the impending problems, settling for less than all hands in is not the best we can do. to those who have returned from overseas, thankyou. i know it's been harder to reacclimate to the first world and stay in touch with family, via ptsd, other issues. know you're appreciated. you deserve health care and people trained to relate to the mental state you come back as, your country not leaving you for dead, accepting you as you are, as you did for us. those kids in texas, i know you fought for freedoms that ensured a better homeland. those kids in cages will grow up as the people you've returned from war as. no reason to settle for less than an america that puts the people who put the welfare of their entire country before their lives, front and center. if the america that people are to return to, is too priveledged and ignorant to accept the people themselves, comeups and problems as we are. then what freedoms are genuinely attainable. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #veteransday #wecandobetter

text:
hey everybody 👋🏻we all know the shit that has happened with musty and what he did to create several victims by the sexual harassment he’s done, alone. i just wanted to say as a last announcement that i am glad to have spoken up about this for when i did. if i hadn’t as well as the other girls who recently did, i don’t think any of us would’ve and probably kept it in the dark. i honestly didn’t want to speak up at first because i thought it was just some random drama that was targeting my friend. but as i looked into the details more, got more evidence and looked into my past conversations with him; it was enough for me to realize a lot of things. don’t blame yourself for not noticing if you didn’t. a lot of people don’t until one speaks up and thankfully several of us did overtime. when you think about it due to this, it brought the whole community together and it’s motherfucking wonderful. that goes without any sense of the sarcastic humor i particularly use 24/7. all you girls are wonderful beautiful human beings. don’t let this scum of the earth take you down; keep your head up high and move on :)!💜💜💜 •
•
•

text:
sometimes you go through things in your life that are awful. hell on earth.  some things are not okay. sometimes you get dealt a really bad hand. forcing yourself to be "positive" and see the bright side of a horrible event isn't necessarily the right way to handle things.  when i was diagnosed with breast cancer,  everyone in my life kept shoving rays of sunshine down my throat. "stay strong" and "fight like a girl"  everyone deals with trauma differently. i was just trying to get through each moment. the year of 2016 was pure hell for me. i was actually kicked out of a breast cancer support group because i was not "positive enough " of course i was going through chemotherapy and having an allergic reaction to the treatment but no one would listen to me. i was just accused of not being "positive enough "  there's some similarities between dealing with domestic abuse and cancer. these are two topics that make people very uncomfortable.  so well meaning people, and others want you to be strong and just move on. but sometimes that's because it's what they need, not what you need. it's okay to say "wow what happened to you was horrible" that's validation and we all should have the freedom to feel whatever emotions we need to.  that's not the same as behaving however you want. feelings and actions are two very different things. feelings aren't good or bad,  it's what you do with them. start where you are. i have been dealt some really lousy cards, but that doesn't mean i have to give up. i feel, i process and i keep moving forward.  that's how you survive. you don't quit. 
#whywomendontleave #domesticabuse #complexptsd #domesticviolence #dv #violenceagainstwomen #narcissist #ptsd#metoo#breastcancersurvivior#cancersucks#cancersurvivor#feelings#empathy#complexptsdawareness#compassion#validation#itsokaytonotbeokay
name: Mother, wife and advocate

text: lest we forget.  in these times of political instability i find myself at a crossroads.  part of why i joined the military was to support the idea that “i may not agree with you, but i will defend to my death your right to say it”. i’m not so sure anymore.  i wish i had the optimistic eyes of 19 year old me digging trenches in the last post.  i don’t know anymore.  but i will not forget the sacrifices made by my grandfather, by my dad and in some ways me. i lost my innocent eyes in the infantry.  that was my first #metoo.  a slap in the face to a bright eyed young woman.  but i believed in what i was doing.  for me.  for my country. 🇨🇦

text:
colabs conversations, hosted by the college of liberal arts & behavioral sciences and odei.

this is an important student forum, lead by a panel from the college, to discuss issues that affects students on campus. this particular conversation revolves around consent, accountability, and sexuality. this is in the wake of the #metoo and #timesup movements and the kavanuagh hearings...national issues and conversations that affect us right home!

wednesday, 11/14 at 11am-12pm and at 1pm-2pm in pab 114. (attend either session). snacks provided!

come join the conversation. your voice and experiences are important and need to be heard!
.
.
.

text:
it really is!! sometimes, it’s hard to believe it. i have definitely had my share of doubts. i face cynicism about love all the time. i haven't been very lucky with love. i've confused it with infatuation. i've had many admirers, proposals and even promises of marriage. i've had a lot of good moments as well as a lot of disappointments but god has always had my back. he keeps me grounded in faith and hope. he has protected me from marrying the wrong guy(s). i know that my husband and knight in armor is out there. my partner in life and love does exist. my lover and the leader of my home is real. i choose to believe and be excited! i also choose to be a warm, loving, godly, woman with goals, aspirations and dreams realized (of course with a sprnkle of sass 😉). i will continue to heal and grow and embrace hope. ▪▪▪▪be encouraged. love is real. i promise. 💜

______________________

text:
“the insta-life”

a few months ago, someone complimented my instagram account, mentioning it is happy + vibrant. i thought about this statement for a few reasons.🤔 while it is an honest representation of moments in my life, it is not my entire life. writing this post because i think it’s important to recognize instagram is a snapshot of someone’s life - what you see is not the whole picture. because i often see happy and fomo-type ig posts 😬, here’s mine... nine year ago, i dealt with health issues and withdrew from family + friends. ironman interviewed me in an article (http://m.ironman.com/triathlon/news/articles/2014/09/heidi-buttery-tahoe-foundation.aspx) i shared part of my journey, with a deeper purpose to draw attention to importance of mental health awareness. you’ll also see my passionate road to becoming an endurance athlete, as described in article. 🏊‍♀️🚴‍♀️🏃‍♀️🏞️⛰️
each year, i reflect in november and this year is no different. immense gratitude for the wisdom i have gained over the past year, lessons learned and friendships made. i embraced my community and opened up to friends - not only did it broadon my friendships and made me realize we are never alone. apart from 2009, i have had share of obstacles, heartbreak, turmoil and loss as many of you may had. 
be kind to each other. as albert schweizer wrote ““in everyone's life, at some time, our inner fire goes out. it is then burst into flame by an encounter with another human being. we should all be thankful for those people who rekindle the inner spirit.” as i am a ‘silver lining’ person, i have many things to be grateful for and wish all of you the best life can bring. ❤️❤️ xo,
heidi

ps. let's break the stigma! 👊

#nami #erasestigma #nutritionbyheidi #gratitude #ohana #friendship #loveandlight 💞 #ironman #realtalk #instalife #metoo #girlpower 💪 #ultrarunner #fightstigma #teamsheeper

text:
"a swimming pool and me thinking about death"
so yesterday was father's day here in sweden and i don't celebrate it. when my dad was drunk he used to tell me "i'm not your dad anymore, you're a awful disgusting girl and i don't want anything with you to do any more." i was a little kid. 
and today i'm listening to these words and that's his fault. it's a part of the consequences he has to take. i'm not his daughter any more and that means i've lost my hero. i've lost my hero. i lost my hero the second he touched me that way he did. i lost my dad, and that man became a stranger to me. therefore i don't celebrate father's day.
📷 12 october 2018

text:
🎤🎧💖new episode 27🎤🎧💖 rape in india continues to shock the world after a spate of high profile sexual assaults in recent years, including the gang-rape and murder of a student on a moving new delhi bus in 2012. that attack brought the conversation about sexual violence to the fore in a country where widespread violence against women had long been quietly accepted. 
that’s news of course but what do you do when rape and sexual assault happens in your own home? by someone you trust? who do you talk to? what do you do? 
karina calver opens up to us about her childhood traumatic experiences and how she’s moved on from being a victim to a survivor! she’s coming out with her memoirs “a girl’s faith” and talks to us about repercussions of her assault, how she councils and advocates for survivors who have walked in her shoes.  link to episode in ig bio 👆🏽🙏🏽💖 nriwoman podcasts are available to listen for free on apple podcast, stitcher, spotify, google play app or wherever you get your podcasts from. 
www.nriwoman.com

text:
do you remember as a kid wishing on a star and expecting it to come true?  as adults we have learned that to make our wishes comes true, we have to do some work; wishing alone does not make it happen! .

yet, at times we struggle to make our wishes come true on our own.  in order to do so, we must step out of our comfort zone into the land of uncertainty and messiness.  those around us might criticize or try to persuade us not to move forward - we’re upsetting the apple cart by doing something different and foreign to others.
.
we begin to doubt ourselves.  we have that criticizing voice inside our head tell us we can’t do it and this isn’t safe for us to do.  we stop pursuing our dream and go back to the status quo - but something doesn’t feel right.  late at night when we see that shining star up in the sky we ask ourselves, “but, what if...?”
.
if this sounds familiar, connect with me.  i’d love to talk and see if there’s a way we can work together to make your wish into a reality.  you’d be surprised what support, encouragement, and accountability can do to make a wish into part of your life. .

click on the link ➡️ @denisestyer to set up a call for us to connect.  let’s do this!  there’s still time! 💜

i don’t know, you guys, here is my face. 👋🏽 back home now from @summit. people curious about it have been asking me the ‘takeaways’ question, so i thought i’d share something similar- a list i made right after summit ended, of things i wanted to do more or less of going forward. i won’t bore you with the entire list (this post is already tldr af), but here are a few:
•
•
❤️ more ❤️
•
in-personness. even if i can listen to the same talk, interview, or artist online later, whenever possible, go in person. because there is magic in the live experience of something, in the random electric connections that happen when you are in a room with other people who care about the same thing. thanks @brentbushnell for this.
•
paying attention to my dreams. i learned that the meaning of two recurring nightmares i’ve had my whole life is that i am competing with myself and the only way these nightmares will stop is if i stop judging myself so harshly and comparing myself to better versions of myself. thanks to manari ushigua for this (not on instagram because shaman).
•
reading books and taking in media created by people of color, women of color. i am already doing this as of the last couple years, but i want even more. after a 22-year education almost exclusively hearing the stories of white men, i am so hungry for the rest of it.
•
focusing on the connections between events and the through lines around me. i loved when tarana burke (creator of the #metoo movement) said about cavanaugh, “i can draw a direct line from that young white boy growing up in a country club and never hearing the word ‘no’ to the man who is now a supreme court justice who believes he can and should make decisions about my body.”
•
reading everything by @anandwrites .
•
thoughtfulness about how i speak about myself and my work. thanks @aviva_klein for one of my favorite conversations from summit.
•
finding role models for the kind of relationship i want to have. thanks @estherperelofficial (hero ❤️) for this.
•
(continued in next post)

text: #digitalart #art #artistsoninstagram #artwork #socialissues #compassion #rapevictim #rapeculture #unpretty #metoo #himtoo just a note: (rare case where i explain motive). as a rape survivor, this was not politically motivated (in the american voting system sense). i’m not american. i wished to express the reminder that the most powerful of men (not just women), are vulnerable to this horrific crime. i also wished to show a powerful man in a way he could be viewed with compassion. i wished to inspire widened perspectives. i don’t feel i did this incredibly important issue justice but i’m just one person with a story. if this is hard to look at, it’s because this crime is horrific. that said, i believe media has made male/female rape common enough for some to be desensitized. it’s a juxtaposition i found worth my humble attempts. wishing you all peace 💗

text: they that stole my innocence and freedom won’t steal anything else from me . i’ll reclaim everything and more if it takes me till my last breath. through every tear i cried and every tear i still cry i know it’s for redemption. i may grieve what i lost but i’m not missing what i have, what is right before me . even in the midst of my darkest days i see ... i feel ... and that is more than what i can say for the ones that hurt me . i’d truly hate to know the things they see and feel . the horror! they only have pleasure in that one moment they are inflicting pain on someone else the rest of their days are muddled and tormented. where as i, we can eventually find peace somewhere... find grace and come up for fresh air on our journeys. #sundayvibes #ptsd #traumarecovery #emdr #grace #journey #mystory #metoo #menaresurvivorstoo ##redemption #crypretty #peace #domesticviolence #grief #freedom #christiansurvivor #suicideprevention #❤️ #speakyourtruth #life #brokenandbeautiful #inthistogether #affirmations #healing

text:
this three day event is a gift from playwright alyson mead, who in the wake of conversations about consent, sexual assualt and rape has graciously given special permission to perform her timely play "the flora and the fauna" across the nation. 
omaha was given permission to perform this show three times, in hopes to reach the wider community. 
all tickets have a $10 suggested donation and all proceeds go to benefit the #metoo movement as we work tirelessly to end sexual assault and rape culture. get tickets at the link in my bio. 
this event features 18 of omaha's finest actors, and we could've cast it 3 times over with the overwhelming support and love we've received from local talent.

reserve your tickets now. share the event. carpool. bring your mothers, husbands, sisters and sons to watch brilliant performances of this searing and honest play. 
the flora and the fauna by alyson mead
directed by amy lane and beth thompson
produced by beaufield berry-fisher
with special thanks to steven williams, valerie st. pierre smith and carol danigle. 
featuring: 
kim jubenville and sonia keffer
connie lee and teri fender
daena schweiger and beth thompson
tammyra' jackson and carrie beth stickrod
felicia webster and madhat kat (ka walsh) 
laura campbell and catherine ann vazquez
jodi vaccaro and be louis
haley piper haas and breanna francesca carodine
de chap and catie zaleski

text: this looks like any other post right? just a picture of joy and who knows what the caption will be. i didn't know what other thing to put at the picture, so i chose something i usually would post. this isn't your regular post of course because this is my post about #metoo. i've joined this tag before and never expected to do it once again. i'm a victim of rape. i was extremely wasted, arguably pressured to drink, and consented to it because i was so done with life and had already planned on committing suicide a month later. i didn't even know the guy, was visiting another 'friend' who i don't want anything to do with anymore, and the one that raped me was sober and had a girlfriend. after it happened i was in so much shock and denial, it really didn't hit me. i made jokes about it thinking it would be better. it's just becoming worse and worse over time. it's slowly eating me alive and my head keeps repeating the same images whenever i'm alone in the dark, or when it gets quiet. i thought it would get better over time unlike the first time i got sexually assaulted. but it just keeps growing because i can never open up about how i feel about it. sure some people know it happened and i brush it off but the more i do so the more it hurts and creeps up on me. i have no idea why i'm sharing this but i feel like this is a step to a healthy change in my life to start fresh and clean from all the bad memories and things that happened this year.

text:
501 years ago this month a concerned catholic nailed a series of 95 theses onto a church door. his was a voice dissenting corruption in the church, thereby setting the stage for an evolution of thought through the reformation. today, groups of concerned catholics in 21 cities across the u.s. are posting their #5theses on church doors. theirs is a woman's voice denouncing the structures that have permitted and perpetuated clergy sexual abuse and that have systematically oppressed women (with next to complete erasure of queer and gender non-confirming folks) - this voice is directed to the u.s. conference of catholic bishops on the eve of their fall general assembly.
.
what is the evolution of thought needed at this time? it's clear a new way of being that embraces radical inclusivity is emerging, and its approach is marked by the stirrings of #metoo, by the visions of a more equitable world brought forth despite, or perhaps because of, the contentious political dialogue, and by a dramatically interconnected global society growing in awareness of the high stakes facing our earthly home.
.
how does all this coincide with this catholic moment? now, far from being untouchable, the church is ever increasingly subject to public and internal criticism. as it should. the patriarchical  governing body is not representative of the church. the church is the body of the faithful. it includes the everyday person, laity, religious, and clergy. honoring this redefinition is to uplift the voice of laity and religious. to believe survivors. to care for creation. this catholic moment is a transformative one. how it transforms and whether that transformation upholds the tenets of love at the core of faith is up to us. just about every 500 years, according to sr. amy hereford, csj, the church and the communities that embody its values reinvent themselves. our 500 year mark is here.
.
today, standing outside st. patrick's cathedral, i pray for: the end of sexual abuse, an end to clericalism, church reform, women's leadership, and healthy conversation on human sexuality. i place these prayers in the hands of those i know: in yours, in mine, and in the invisible one who carries us.

text:
a year ago today, i was sexually assaulted by a friend; someone i trusted very much. this caused me to spiral into severe self-destruction. i got kicked off my football team because i couldn't leave my room, i stopped going to church because i felt guilty, and i stopped going to band rehearsal because i couldn't be in the same room as him. i have so many people to thank for helping me stay alive as long as i have, and i want to thank god first and foremost. i decided to dedicate an entire chapter of my book to this trauma, and i received a lot of support but also a lot of backlash for being "too vulnerable". i wrote the chapter "trauma" in gold mouth not for sympathy, but for awareness. no means no, and you should never have to explain why. instead of teaching women how to become robotic human beings, why don't we teach men how to respect women and not be sexual predators. i want to thank my sisters in christ for being there for me today, and i'm so thankful you are all in my life.💛
-
#feminist #nomeansno #metoo #goldmouth #traumaanniversary #mentalillness #mentalhealth

text:
"panty portrait: muff" from the panty project, 4 of 51
.

fiber art, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 
19 x 14 inches
.
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

day 1 : truth 
what is your truth, despite anything that has happened?
how can you tell your body “i am safe to release this pain now, i love you, i’m so sorry. i am leaning into my strength now”

after the wounding, the healing.  healing takes time and is not linear.  it does not mean you are non-functioning. 
the truth is i am a hero of my own journey. “everything i’ve ever done, everything i’ve ever learned,” she says, “i’m using all of that stuff right now. and all the women that reside in me are now operative.” ~97 year old female park ranger

i am finally accepting more parts of myself and listening to my body more…by saying, thank you, i love you <3
